            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="299" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The European Recovery Program–Trade Union Conference, established in March 1948,
                    held a second conference in London July 29–30. In despatch 1755 from London,
                    August 13, 1948, not printed, First Secretary Samuel D. Berger reported that
                    U.S. labor leaders believed that the Conference’s lack of action could be
                    attributed to the “negative attitude of the <gloss target="#t_TUC1">T.U.C.</gloss>”</p>
            </div>
        </body>
